This approach is similar to the approach used when the 'it' test block is async, except we must wrap the contents of the beforeEach inside of an async(() =>{...}) function, like so:

beforeEach(
      async(() => {
        TestBed.configureTestingModule({
          imports: [FormsModule],
          declarations: [ShoppingEditComponent],
          providers: [
            provideMockStore({ initialState: { ...mockDefaultAppState } })
          ]
        });
        TestBed.compileComponents();
        fixture = TestBed.createComponent(ShoppingEditComponent);
        component = fixture.componentInstance;
        shoppingEditElement = fixture.debugElement.nativeElement;
        store = TestBed.get<Store<fromApp.AppState>>(Store);
}));

then, we can run a fakeAsync type test with our fixture and other vars already defined

If you're going to call funcs like 'tick()' inside of your beforeEach block, then change async(() => {...}) to fakeAsync(() => {...})


